    {
        "id": "57b6373ed38c4eba",
        "type": "comment",
        "z": "792ae5b2f20bb202",
        "g": "6beef9b705494822",
        "name": "Function Flow Notes (ReadMe)",
        "info": "Flow Notes (Fan Control Subflow)\n--------------------------------\n- Speed > 1 = Fan ON\n- Speed = 0 (or 1 due to ESP quirk) = Fan OFF\n- Mycodo publishes fan speed → keeps dashboard synced\n- Output #2 loops back into dashboard switch to mirror state\n- ⚠️ Switch node option \"Pass through messages\" MUST be OFF\n   → Prevents infinite feedback loop when updating state\n   2nd flow.set function from MQTT Speed updates speed context\n   without causing feedback loop. Maintains speed through\n   NodeRed 'deploy when spped set through Mycodo.\n- MQTT topics use fixed fan_id inside subflow (can’t inherit)",
        "x": 650,
        "y": 200,
        "wires": []
    },
